89
00:06:01,094 --> 00:06:04,055
and even from your mistress
to sell contracts to be our partners.

90
00:06:04,139 --> 00:06:07,809
Wait a second.
I think you've been hearing rumors.

91
00:06:07,892 --> 00:06:09,436
You even hired a D-list celebrity

92
00:06:09,519 --> 00:06:11,938
for the company ad
just because he's your nephew.

93
00:06:12,022 --> 00:06:13,189
I saw it at the airport.

94
00:06:13,273 --> 00:06:15,066
No, that's…

95
00:06:17,318 --> 00:06:19,446
You must have thought it was okay
to take advantage of our company like that

96
00:06:20,113 --> 00:06:22,907
since the chairman's turned
a blind eye to what you do.

97
00:06:28,371 --> 00:06:30,707
President Kang, listen.
It's not like that.

98
00:06:30,790 --> 00:06:34,794
I've been inattentive to company matters,
spending so much time abroad.

99
00:06:34,878 --> 00:06:36,921
I intend to pay closer attention
from now on.

100
00:06:41,009 --> 00:06:43,720
I'll see you tomorrow, then, Mr. Park.

101
00:06:46,723 --> 00:06:48,808
Hey, President Kang!

102
00:06:48,892 --> 00:06:50,602
Wait, President Kang!

103
00:06:50,685 --> 00:06:52,145
President Kang.

104
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,315
Mr. Park! Are you okay?

105
00:06:55,398 --> 00:06:56,691
-What is this?
-Damn it.

106
00:06:56,775 --> 00:06:59,110
-What's going on?
-What is this?

107
00:07:16,294 --> 00:07:20,715
Since it's Ms. Shin's birthday, I made
reservations at Auntie's Street Food

108
00:07:20,799 --> 00:07:23,301
for our team dinner today.
Ms. Shin's favorite!

109
00:07:23,385 --> 00:07:25,428
All right. How long has it been?

110
00:07:25,512 --> 00:07:28,306
Oh, you guys didn't have to do that
just for my birthday.

111
00:07:28,390 --> 00:07:29,599
Thank you.

112
00:07:29,682 --> 00:07:32,602
What are you talking about?
A team's got to stick together.

113
00:07:32,685 --> 00:07:33,645
You're buying, right?

114
00:07:34,854 --> 00:07:35,814
Great!

115
00:07:35,897 --> 00:07:38,608
<i>Happy birthday. Can you swing by?
I have something for you.</i>

116
00:07:41,361 --> 00:07:45,865
Ms. Yeo, I'm sorry, but I don't think
I can make it to the team dinner today.

117
00:07:45,949 --> 00:07:47,700
Why? What is it?

118
00:07:48,535 --> 00:07:49,869
Is it a guy?

119
00:07:50,495 --> 00:07:51,454
How did you know?

120
00:07:51,538 --> 00:07:56,626
Because your soulless eyes
are suddenly sparkling. That's how.

121
00:07:57,168 --> 00:07:58,878
Okay, go on.

122
00:08:01,256 --> 00:08:03,925
It looks like we'll have to celebrate
Ms. Shin's birthday

123
00:08:04,008 --> 00:08:05,510
without the birthday girl.

124
00:08:06,219 --> 00:08:08,346
An inauguration without the president,

125
00:08:08,430 --> 00:08:10,807
and a birthday party
without the birthday girl?

126
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:11,975
What's going on?

127
00:08:12,058 --> 00:08:15,395
Seriously. This is like celebrating
Thanksgiving without a turkey.

128
00:08:16,229 --> 00:08:18,773
I'm sorry.
I promise the next dinner is on me!

129
00:08:18,857 --> 00:08:20,316
I'm sorry.

130
00:08:33,246 --> 00:08:34,122
Hello?

131
00:08:34,205 --> 00:08:35,415
Ha-ri!

132
00:08:35,498 --> 00:08:38,793
I'm so busy, I can't even meet up
with you on your birthday.

133
00:08:38,877 --> 00:08:40,378
So what's my girl got planned?

134
00:08:40,462 --> 00:08:42,881
Min-woo wants to see me,
so I'm heading over.

135
00:08:42,964 --> 00:08:44,340
One moment.

136
00:08:44,424 --> 00:08:45,884
Min-woo?

137
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:47,760
Why is he calling you on your birthday?

138
00:08:47,844 --> 00:08:50,221
After he made you
do all that work for his new menu?

139
00:08:50,305 --> 00:08:53,808
That was hardly work.
I had a blast, and I learned a lot too.

140
00:08:53,892 --> 00:08:57,687
<i>Goodness, you're really head-over-heels
for Min-woo.</i>

141
00:08:57,770 --> 00:09:00,773
But he's never been the type
to remember birthdays. Why is he--

142
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:04,110
Wait, no way!

143
00:09:04,194 --> 00:09:05,111
No way, what?

144
00:09:05,195 --> 00:09:07,489
Was that necklace from before
really your birthday gift?

145
00:09:07,572 --> 00:09:08,615
Necklace?

146
00:09:19,709 --> 00:09:21,127
Why is a woman's necklace here?

147
00:09:21,711 --> 00:09:23,838
Maybe some customer left it behind.

148
00:09:24,714 --> 00:09:27,383
There's even a certificate
of authenticity!

149
00:09:28,593 --> 00:09:30,553
Look, this is garnet!

150
00:09:30,637 --> 00:09:31,804
That's my birthstone.

151
00:09:31,888 --> 00:09:33,640
Is he dating a girl born in January?

152
00:09:33,723 --> 00:09:35,892
Remember that foreign model girl?

153
00:09:35,975 --> 00:09:38,561
She went back to her country
after Min-woo rejected her.

154
00:09:38,645 --> 00:09:41,731
Then is it that journalist
writing an article on his restaurant?

155
00:09:41,814 --> 00:09:44,901
She was flirting with Min-woo
but stopped after he friendzoned her.

156
00:09:44,984 --> 00:09:45,985
The YouTuber then!

157
00:09:46,069 --> 00:09:48,404
That YouTuber?
She asked him out on a livestream.

158
00:09:48,488 --> 00:09:50,740
