159
00:09:51,699 --> 00:09:54,244
Maybe it's your birthday present.

160
00:09:54,327 --> 00:09:56,037
You think? Let me see.

161
00:09:56,663 --> 00:09:59,999
No, this is way too expensive
to buy for a friend.

162
00:10:00,083 --> 00:10:01,709
-Right?
-Yeah.

163
00:10:15,682 --> 00:10:16,933
<i>It has to be!</i>

164
00:10:17,016 --> 00:10:19,310
That necklace really was for you!

165
00:10:19,394 --> 00:10:22,063
You said that it was too expensive
to buy for a friend.

166
00:10:22,897 --> 00:10:24,524
Well, what if he's planning to transfer

167
00:10:24,607 --> 00:10:26,985
from the friendship train
to the boyfriend express?

168
00:10:27,068 --> 00:10:30,613
<i>If you are transferring to Train 6,
please exit at the next stop.</i>

169
00:10:30,697 --> 00:10:32,907
<i>The exit is to the right.</i>

170
00:10:46,170 --> 00:10:49,465
-Has the inauguration been taken care of?
-Yes, it went well.

171
00:10:51,467 --> 00:10:52,802
What about the chairman?

172
00:10:58,391 --> 00:11:00,476
You crazy bastard.

173
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:03,146
I told you to come to the inauguration.
You blow me off.

174
00:11:03,229 --> 00:11:06,065
I told you to meet me at the house,
but you meet me at work.

175
00:11:06,149 --> 00:11:08,359
You're determined to go against me,
aren't you?

176
00:11:08,443 --> 00:11:10,903
Of course not. I've simply been too busy.

177
00:11:10,987 --> 00:11:14,324
You just flew back in today!
You can't take a single damn day off?

178
00:11:14,407 --> 00:11:17,785
No, I can't. There are too many things
that need to be taken care of.

179
00:11:17,869 --> 00:11:19,454
