go with a guy and not with Young-seo.

249
00:15:48,014 --> 00:15:49,015
Okay.

250
00:15:49,849 --> 00:15:51,017
Go on.

251
00:15:56,314 --> 00:15:59,317
You have no clue what I really like.

252
00:16:02,945 --> 00:16:04,572
Good going.

253
00:16:04,655 --> 00:16:09,452
You're eating instant food
as your first meal back in Korea

254
00:16:09,535 --> 00:16:13,289
when you know how to cook everything
from Korean to Western!

255
00:16:13,372 --> 00:16:18,252
Wouldn't it be nice
to sit at the dinner table with your wife

256
00:16:18,336 --> 00:16:20,463
and enjoy a good home-cooked meal?

257
00:16:20,546 --> 00:16:22,632
I'm not getting married just for that.

258
00:16:22,715 --> 00:16:26,385
I hear American women are beautiful.

259
00:16:26,469 --> 00:16:30,056
Did you really not date at all?
I'm open-minded, you know.

260
00:16:30,139 --> 00:16:32,934
I have no time for that.
I'm busy enough with work.

261
00:16:33,017 --> 00:16:37,104
That's why I've scheduled
your blind dates for you. So--

262
00:16:37,188 --> 00:16:39,273
I told you I'm not interested, didn't I?

263
00:16:43,945 --> 00:16:47,073
Are you two dating?

264
00:16:47,823 --> 00:16:48,658
-What?
-What?

265
00:16:48,741 --> 00:16:49,951
It seems that way.

266
00:16:50,034 --> 00:16:52,745
You two are joined at the hip,
using work as an excuse.

267
00:16:52,828 --> 00:16:54,622
I don't know about him, but I'm not gay.

268
00:16:54,705 --> 00:16:56,874
And even if I liked men,

269
00:16:58,209 --> 00:17:01,837
-President Kang isn't really my style.
-Is that so? Not your style?

270
00:17:02,630 --> 00:17:04,590
Hey, what do you mean?
What's wrong with me?

271
00:17:04,674 --> 00:17:06,968
Fine. If you're not, you're not.

272
00:17:07,677 --> 00:17:10,346
Then why are you
so against going on these dates?

273
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,768
What is it now?

274
00:17:16,435 --> 00:17:17,770
ALARM 10 P.M.
TIME TO TAKE BLOOD PRESSURE MEDS

275
00:17:17,853 --> 00:17:19,063
Ah, shoot…

276
00:17:19,146 --> 00:17:21,732
I can take care of myself,
so just go watch your TV shows.

277
00:17:21,816 --> 00:17:23,192
Isn't that alarm for them?

278
00:17:23,275 --> 00:17:25,569
It's for my blood pressure medication!

279
00:17:25,653 --> 00:17:28,197
My blood pressure is so high nowadays
because of you.

280
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:30,408
I'm taking pills every day!

281
00:17:30,491 --> 00:17:32,868
How is that my fault?
It runs in the family.

282
00:17:32,952 --> 00:17:35,413
It'd be your fault
if I got high blood pressure.

283
00:17:35,496 --> 00:17:36,539
You little--

284
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:41,585
<i>I'm calling your name</i>

285
00:17:41,669 --> 00:17:45,256
<i>But the sun sets quietly
Without a response</i>

286
00:17:45,339 --> 00:17:46,882
SHIN JOONG-HAE AND THE WILDFLOWERS
GUITAR CLUB MEETING

287
00:17:49,051 --> 00:17:50,011
Thank you.

288
00:17:50,094 --> 00:17:52,722
Hey, everyone, help yourselves.

289
00:17:53,222 --> 00:17:54,140
Eat up, guys.

290
00:17:54,223 --> 00:17:55,182
Okay.

291
00:17:55,266 --> 00:17:57,059
-Cheers!
-Bottoms up!

292
00:17:57,143 --> 00:17:58,686
Cheers!

293
00:18:10,364 --> 00:18:13,451
-Sir, can I get some more of these chips?
-Go ahead.

294
00:18:13,534 --> 00:18:15,578
-Mom!
-Gosh, what? You scared me!

295
00:18:16,078 --> 00:18:19,749
I told you that you have to coat
the chicken properly to make it crispy.

296
00:18:19,832 --> 00:18:22,334
I told you you have to be thorough.

297
00:18:22,418 --> 00:18:24,128
But I am tossing it!

298
00:18:24,211 --> 00:18:28,507
If we're not going to do things right,
we should just close up shop.

299
00:18:28,591 --> 00:18:32,511
I guess that's why
the chicken Ha-ri makes tastes better.

300
00:18:32,595 --> 00:18:33,429
You're the best!

301
00:18:34,013 --> 00:18:38,642
Of course! She works at a major company,
after all. She's different.

302
00:18:38,726 --> 00:18:41,437
Why are you so edgy today?

303
00:18:42,146 --> 00:18:45,232
It can't feel great to have to work
on your birthday, of all days.

304
00:18:45,316 --> 00:18:48,444
So what? I'm the one
who gave birth after 20 hours of labor!

305
00:18:50,112 --> 00:18:53,282
Toss and toss and toss…

306
00:18:56,535 --> 00:18:57,703
Will he be all right?

307
00:18:57,787 --> 00:19:01,248
Yes. His blood pressure's higher
than usual, but it's not serious.

308
00:19:01,332 --> 00:19:03,167
What do you mean, it's not serious?

309
00:19:03,250 --> 00:19:05,711
Last time, you said that my lungs,

310
00:19:05,795 --> 00:19:08,672
kidneys, and small intestine
weren't doing great.

311
00:19:08,756 --> 00:19:09,757
What? I did?

312
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:11,759
Doctor!

313
00:19:12,301 --> 00:19:14,845
Oh, yes, that's right. I remember now.

314
00:19:15,387 --> 00:19:18,599
Considering his age,
things can change drastically day by day.

315
00:19:18,682 --> 00:19:21,811
And you said I should avoid stress
more than anything, right?

316
00:19:21,894 --> 00:19:22,728
Yes, sir.

317
00:19:22,812 --> 00:19:25,940
-Everyone around him should be careful.
-Did you hear that?

318
00:19:26,023 --> 00:19:29,276
It seems you're fine,
so drop the act and get out of bed.

319
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:33,447
You! Do you really want
to see me die because of you?

320
00:19:33,531 --> 00:19:34,824
I'm going to--

321
00:19:34,907 --> 00:19:37,910
Since you're already here,
why don't you get a full checkup?

322
00:19:37,993 --> 00:19:39,245
I'm leaving.

323
00:19:43,874 --> 00:19:47,962
SEOUL KANGSUNG HOSPITAL

324
00:20:05,020 --> 00:20:06,939
What's the point of group reservations?

325
00:20:07,523 --> 00:20:09,108
You give them a discount,

326
00:20:09,191 --> 00:20:11,193
and they just fill up on the free snacks.

327
00:20:14,196 --> 00:20:17,366
Why has she been so grumpy all day?

328
00:20:18,409 --> 00:20:19,702
Hey, Ha-ri.

329
00:20:19,785 --> 00:20:23,455
Don't you have a boyfriend who can throw
you a birthday party or something?

330
00:20:24,039 --> 00:20:25,916
I didn't leave anything in front of

331
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,501
-your store!
-What's going on?

332
00:20:27,585 --> 00:20:29,461
I told you I saw it! This is yours!

333
00:20:29,545 --> 00:20:31,463
You've got a big mouth for a kid!

334
00:20:31,547 --> 00:20:32,506
-Yes, I do!
-What?

335
00:20:32,590 --> 00:20:34,216
-Hey.
-What? What is it?

336
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:36,093
Why is this in front of our store?

337
00:20:36,177 --> 00:20:37,595
I put it there for a minute

338
00:20:37,678 --> 00:20:39,972
because a customer parked
in front of our store!

339
00:20:40,055 --> 00:20:42,683
I know you put it here
whenever you get the chance.

340
00:20:42,766 --> 00:20:43,976
Did you see me do it?

341
00:20:44,059 --> 00:20:46,478
It's obvious!
We find fish bones all the time!

342
00:20:46,562 --> 00:20:48,522
We don't sell fish! We sell chicken.

343
00:20:48,606 --> 00:20:50,608
-Take it.
-We don't sell fish either.

344
00:20:50,691 --> 00:20:53,611
It says it right there.
"Fish, dried fish, mackerel, so on."

345
00:20:53,694 --> 00:20:54,653
-Take it.
-Honey, come on.

346
00:20:54,737 --> 00:20:58,032
We're all neighbors here. There's no need
to fight. Let's talk it out.

347
00:20:58,115 --> 00:21:01,202
-I'm doing this so we don't have to fight.
-Come on, take it!

348
00:21:01,702 --> 00:21:04,371
This is a new shirt!
I had it shipped from abroad!

349
00:21:04,455 --> 00:21:08,167
-You toss it! Do what you want with it!
-Hey, don't shove it at him!

350
00:21:08,918 --> 00:21:10,211
I didn't…

351
00:21:13,464 --> 00:21:15,382
You were the one who started it!

352
00:21:16,634 --> 00:21:17,468
Get in here.

353
00:21:20,721 --> 00:21:24,558
Man, breaking the neighbor's store sign
and everything…

354
00:21:24,642 --> 00:21:26,352
I feel so bad.

355
00:21:26,936 --> 00:21:29,605
Everyone in the Shin family
has such a temper!

356
00:21:30,189 --> 00:21:33,692
As if it wasn't enough that Ha-min
started fighting, why did you do that?

357
00:21:33,776 --> 00:21:35,986
I got this temper from you, Mom.

358
00:21:36,695 --> 00:21:39,073
Yes, why are you blaming it on the Shins?

359
00:21:39,156 --> 00:21:41,742
What? Since when did you two
get along so well?

360
00:21:41,825 --> 00:21:44,787
You guys just have to
talk back like that, don't you?

361
00:21:44,870 --> 00:21:47,414
It's because I take after you, Mom!

362
00:21:47,957 --> 00:21:49,291
It's my birthday!

363
00:21:50,292 --> 00:21:51,335
Why are you hitting me?

364
00:21:53,045 --> 00:21:55,172
You can't keep on using that as an excuse!

365
00:21:57,967 --> 00:22:00,761
I made you seaweed soup in the morning!
Isn't that enough?

366
00:22:02,554 --> 00:22:05,349
You forgot to cook her seaweed soup today.

367
00:22:06,350 --> 00:22:07,851
Just stop it.

368
00:22:17,778 --> 00:22:20,656
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, HA-RI
FROM MIN-WOO

369
00:22:25,494 --> 00:22:26,870
<i>Happy birthday, Ha-ri.</i>

370
00:22:27,371 --> 00:22:29,623
<i>Tickets to your favorite singer's concert.</i>

371
00:22:29,707 --> 00:22:33,293
<i>They weren't easy to get, so make sure you
go with a guy and not with Young-seo.</i>

372
00:22:55,733 --> 00:22:58,110
Fine. I said, fine.

373
00:22:59,737 --> 00:23:02,031
Did you have a good night's sleep?

374
00:23:11,290 --> 00:23:16,170
-I have something to tell you.
-I just got a call from Mr. Park.

375
00:23:16,253 --> 00:23:19,048
So you're aware of the situation?
I'm going to fire Mr. Park.

376
00:23:19,131 --> 00:23:20,966
What? Says who?

377
00:23:21,050 --> 00:23:24,219
He selected the subcontractors illegally.

378
00:23:24,845 --> 00:23:29,641
But he still did a lot for the company
working under your predecessor.

379
00:23:29,725 --> 00:23:31,769
He built a summer house
on our company land.

380
00:23:31,852 --> 00:23:34,938
And he used our employees
for his personal affairs.

381
00:23:35,022 --> 00:23:37,483
He'll do it all over again
if we let him be.

382
00:23:42,988 --> 00:23:44,364
Park's father is Sang-gu,

383
00:23:44,448 --> 00:23:49,620
my good old friend who contributed
greatly to our company's success.

384
00:23:49,703 --> 00:23:52,664
He asked me to take care
of his son for him when he passed--

385
00:23:52,748 --> 00:23:55,793
You can take care of him personally
after letting him go.

386
00:23:55,876 --> 00:23:57,086
Come on.

387
00:23:58,337 --> 00:23:59,797
Then,

388
00:24:00,881 --> 00:24:02,424
do me a favor in return.

389
00:24:04,009 --> 00:24:04,927
Go on the dates!

390
00:24:06,970 --> 00:24:10,057
-Grandfather, that's--
-Stop making excuses and just do it.

391
00:24:10,140 --> 00:24:13,102
I'm breaking the promise
I made to my dead friend.

392
00:24:13,185 --> 00:24:15,938
It's the least you could do.

393
00:24:22,027 --> 00:24:24,446
Fine, I'll go on the dates.

394
00:24:24,530 --> 00:24:27,324
You mean it? Really?

395
00:24:27,407 --> 00:24:29,201
Ms. Ahn, you heard it too, right?

396
00:24:29,284 --> 00:24:31,370
-Yes, sir.
-You're my witness, okay?

397
00:24:31,453 --> 00:24:32,579
All right.

398
00:24:33,163 --> 00:24:35,958
Ha-ri, why did you have to go
and lose your temper?

399
00:24:36,041 --> 00:24:38,710
Wait, the total is 800,000 won…

400
00:24:38,794 --> 00:24:43,423
My tiny monthly pay minus
money for my savings, work loan,

401
00:24:43,507 --> 00:24:46,635
and spending money…
I barely have anything left.

402
00:24:46,718 --> 00:24:50,764
Where am I going to get 800,000 won?

403
00:24:54,935 --> 00:24:56,311
-Did you hear?
-Oh, my God!

404
00:24:57,104 --> 00:24:59,231
You don't know?
I'm the only one who's heard?

405
00:24:59,314 --> 00:25:01,150
Don't freak out, okay?

406
00:25:01,233 --> 00:25:03,402
Mr. Park got fired.

407
00:25:03,485 --> 00:25:05,487
-What?
-Are you sure you heard right?

408
00:25:05,571 --> 00:25:08,115
He's one of the chairman's men,
but he got fired?

409
00:25:08,198 --> 00:25:09,449
Why did they fire him?

410
00:25:09,533 --> 00:25:12,661
Apparently, he's been accepting bribes
from the subcontractors.

411
00:25:12,744 --> 00:25:16,498
I heard President Kang is really strict.
So it's true.

412
00:25:16,582 --> 00:25:18,083
I know, right?

413
00:25:19,168 --> 00:25:20,794
You guys don't seem shocked, though.

414
00:25:26,175 --> 00:25:27,301
Hi, Young-seo.

415
00:25:28,886 --> 00:25:34,266
So you got ahead of yourself and ended up
completely ruining somebody's event.

416
00:25:34,349 --> 00:25:37,311
Hey, you're partially responsible.
You put ideas into my head.

417
00:25:37,394 --> 00:25:38,395
INCOMING CALL
BIOLOGICAL FATHER

418
00:25:38,478 --> 00:25:42,399
"Biological father"?
Did you fight with your dad again?

419
00:25:42,482 --> 00:25:44,484
When were we ever on good terms?

420
00:25:44,568 --> 00:25:46,195
Why is he calling me at this hour?

421
00:25:52,284 --> 00:25:56,163
How could he tell me
about a blind date on the day of?

422
00:25:56,246 --> 00:25:57,080
MANNA SNACK BAR

423
00:25:57,164 --> 00:25:59,333
But I thought blind dates
were off the table

424
00:25:59,416 --> 00:26:01,835
after you faked that exorcism
on your last one.

425
00:26:01,919 --> 00:26:03,420
You're still getting offers?

426
00:26:03,503 --> 00:26:07,132
I suppose the rumors didn't spread
as much as I had thought.

427
00:26:08,258 --> 00:26:09,551
Damn it!

428
00:26:12,221 --> 00:26:13,472
Wait for me.

429
00:26:13,555 --> 00:26:15,933
So, who is it this time?
Is it the Dongseong Group?

430
00:26:16,516 --> 00:26:17,684
Daemin Group?

431
00:26:17,768 --> 00:26:20,270
I don't know. I didn't even ask.

432
00:26:20,812 --> 00:26:23,357
I'm so busy with work already.

433
00:26:24,566 --> 00:26:27,319
Rather than getting wrinkles
from working overtime,

434
00:26:28,070 --> 00:26:31,365
isn't going on a blind date
with a wealthy guy more productive?

435
00:26:31,448 --> 00:26:36,119
No, I'm never doing an arranged marriage.

436
00:26:36,203 --> 00:26:40,040
I'm only going to marry out of love
with someone I meet through fate.

437
00:26:41,083 --> 00:26:43,669
You're so spoiled,
talking about fate and all that.

438
00:26:45,045 --> 00:26:46,213
So I was thinking.

439
00:26:46,797 --> 00:26:48,882
I'm going to need your help again.

440
00:26:49,758 --> 00:26:52,844
Hey, I told you I'd stop doing that
once I got a job.

441
00:26:52,928 --> 00:26:54,137
I'll pass.

442
00:26:55,931 --> 00:26:57,766
This is the last time, I swear!

443
00:26:57,849 --> 00:27:01,228
Can't you just pretend
to be possessed just one more time

444
00:27:01,311 --> 00:27:03,730
so I can stop going on
these blind dates for good?

445
00:27:11,363 --> 00:27:14,116
You must be nervous.
You haven't said a word.

446
00:27:16,159 --> 00:27:18,662
-What's wrong, Young-seo?
-No.

447
00:27:18,745 --> 00:27:21,456
-No.
-Young-seo, are you all right?

448
00:27:21,540 --> 00:27:22,708
Let go!

449
00:27:25,794 --> 00:27:28,171
Do you have any idea
who you're addressing?

450
00:27:30,048 --> 00:27:33,010
How dare you approach the noble host

451
00:27:33,593 --> 00:27:36,179
of the spirit of the great general,
you filthy mortal?

452
00:27:36,263 --> 00:27:37,764
Spirit of the great general?

453
00:27:38,348 --> 00:27:40,183
What's that?

454
00:27:42,311 --> 00:27:44,062
What the hell are you doing?

455
00:27:44,146 --> 00:27:45,814
-What's gotten into you?
-Stay still.

456
00:27:45,897 --> 00:27:48,108
If you value your life, stay still.

457
00:27:49,359 --> 00:27:54,865
What have you done to make such a vengeful
maiden spirit attach herself to you?

458
00:28:03,457 --> 00:28:05,584
Am I the only one who can see the ghost--

459
00:28:07,085 --> 00:28:10,255
<i>I looked up the heir of Daepoong Group,
and he was a huge playboy.</i>

460
00:28:10,339 --> 00:28:14,551
<i>So I tossed in the maiden spirit part.
He was so terrified.</i>

461
00:28:16,970 --> 00:28:19,348
That's what I'm talking about.

462
00:28:19,848 --> 00:28:21,975
Can you help me out again? Please?

463
00:28:22,059 --> 00:28:23,644
No, do it yourself.

464
00:28:24,227 --> 00:28:27,939
Come on,
my acting will only get me so far.

465
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,025
Help me.

466
00:28:31,276 --> 00:28:34,488
No. I'm uncomfortable
with so many people knowing my face.

467
00:28:35,405 --> 00:28:36,823
I'll pay you.

468
00:28:40,118 --> 00:28:41,620
What? Tonight at seven?

469
00:28:41,703 --> 00:28:44,206
Yes, sir. At the coffee shop
at the Imperial Hotel.

470
00:28:44,289 --> 00:28:46,166
With Jin Young-seo from the Marine Group.

471
00:28:46,249 --> 00:28:49,252
I have a full schedule today.
Tell them I'm busy.

472
00:28:50,921 --> 00:28:55,008
<i>I don't want to hear you say anything
about being too busy.</i>

473
00:28:55,092 --> 00:28:58,136
<i>Sung-hoon, move some things around
and make the time.</i>

474
00:28:58,220 --> 00:29:01,098
<i>This is exactly why I pay you so much.</i>

475
00:29:01,682 --> 00:29:04,685
And that's why I went ahead
and cleared your schedule.

476
00:29:04,768 --> 00:29:06,812
It was easier at the overseas branch.

477
00:29:06,895 --> 00:29:10,607
I hope you find a suitable partner
among the top ten candidates.

478
00:29:11,191 --> 00:29:12,109
Why is that?

479
00:29:12,192 --> 00:29:14,569
Number 11 is in Japan
and 17 is in Switzerland.

480
00:29:14,653 --> 00:29:16,822
Do you want to travel
that far for a blind date?

481
00:29:16,905 --> 00:29:17,989
What?

482
00:29:18,073 --> 00:29:20,575
Or just get married
like the chairman wants.

483
00:29:20,659 --> 00:29:23,495
Then I won't have to bother
with making time in your schedule

484
00:29:23,578 --> 00:29:26,039
and you won't
have to waste any more time--

485
00:29:26,123 --> 00:29:28,458
I'm just frustrated, that's all.

486
00:29:28,542 --> 00:29:32,170
I mean, I get where
the chairman is coming from.

487
00:29:32,254 --> 00:29:33,505
No.

488
00:29:34,339 --> 00:29:35,966
I think it's a good idea.

489
00:29:38,385 --> 00:29:39,678
Marriage.

490
00:29:48,562 --> 00:29:50,272
Hello.

491
00:29:51,189 --> 00:29:52,858
