00:45:06,445 --> 00:45:10,366
-Where did you get the money?
-I got a bonus from work.

745
00:45:10,867 --> 00:45:14,370
Didn't you say things at work were weird
because of the new president?

746
00:45:14,453 --> 00:45:16,539
But he handed out bonuses right away?

747
00:45:16,622 --> 00:45:18,291
He seems pretty cool.

748
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:21,794
Did you see him? Didn't you say
he's the chairman's grandson?

749
00:45:21,878 --> 00:45:23,629
-What does he look like?
-I don't know.

750
00:45:23,713 --> 00:45:26,382
-Is he handsome?
-I don't know!

751
00:45:26,465 --> 00:45:28,759
Why are you asking me? Don't ask!

752
00:45:29,343 --> 00:45:30,344
Goodness.

753
00:45:31,387 --> 00:45:33,598
Why are you throwing a fit?

754
00:45:33,681 --> 00:45:35,725
Who else would I ask?

755
00:45:35,808 --> 00:45:38,144
She put on a show to stop folding boxes.

756
00:45:38,227 --> 00:45:39,979
Hey, Ha-ri, get your butt back here.

757
00:45:40,605 --> 00:45:42,940
She must be tired. Let her rest.

758
00:45:43,024 --> 00:45:45,318
I'll fold the boxes twice as fast.

759
00:45:45,401 --> 00:45:47,445
-Make that three times.
-Okay!

760
00:45:58,039 --> 00:45:59,707
Hello?

761
00:45:59,790 --> 00:46:03,461
I'm hiding out in a hotel right now
because of you, my friend.

762
00:46:03,544 --> 00:46:04,587
<i>Why a hotel?</i>

763
00:46:04,670 --> 00:46:07,173
Ever since President Kang
said he wanted to marry me,

764
00:46:07,256 --> 00:46:10,760
my old man's been trying to get
our families to meet up! So I ran!

765
00:46:11,886 --> 00:46:13,054
What are you going to do?

766
00:46:13,888 --> 00:46:16,224
You'd better clean up your mess.

767
00:46:16,307 --> 00:46:17,725
How is this my fault?

768
00:46:18,309 --> 00:46:21,771
If he wants to marry you
even after the crazy act I pulled,

769
00:46:21,854 --> 00:46:24,023
I'm sure he's after your family.

770
00:46:25,107 --> 00:46:25,983
You think so?

771
00:46:26,567 --> 00:46:29,111
People who have it all are
always the ones who want more.

772
00:46:29,195 --> 00:46:31,614
His family's much wealthier than mine.

773
00:46:31,697 --> 00:46:33,991
I told you we should go
with the exorcism stuff.

774
00:46:34,075 --> 00:46:38,162
I'll bet my right hand and empty wallet
that he still would've wanted to marry you

775
00:46:38,246 --> 00:46:40,623
even if we went all out with an exorcism.

776
00:46:40,706 --> 00:46:42,833
So what do I do now?

777
00:46:43,918 --> 00:46:45,336
Should I run away from home?

778
00:46:45,419 --> 00:46:47,255
Or shave my head and become a monk?

779
00:46:47,338 --> 00:46:49,757
Just meet President Kang
and tell him honestly.

780
00:46:49,840 --> 00:46:52,927
Tell him that the woman he wants
to marry isn't Jin Young-seo,

781
00:46:53,010 --> 00:46:56,264
that you sent someone else
to ruin the blind date.

782
00:46:56,347 --> 00:46:59,892
Damn it, my dad is going to be so mad.

783
00:46:59,976 --> 00:47:02,436
But it'll stop all of this talk
about marriage.

784
00:47:03,688 --> 00:47:08,109
Just look on the bright side.
It's like a blessing in disguise.

785
00:47:08,693 --> 00:47:12,071
Wait, what if I run
into President Kang at work?

786
00:47:12,154 --> 00:47:13,447
Dang.

787
00:47:14,031 --> 00:47:15,783
I'm getting goosebumps.

788
00:47:15,866 --> 00:47:16,742
<i>Hey.</i>

789
00:47:16,826 --> 00:47:20,329
A regular employee will never
run into the president at work.

790
00:47:20,413 --> 00:47:22,081
-<i>Don't worry about it.</i>
-You think so?

791
00:47:23,291 --> 00:47:24,625
Oh, wait.

792
00:47:33,217 --> 00:47:34,135
Wait for me!

793
00:47:34,218 --> 00:47:39,307
Damn it! Mr. Gye always gives me hell
if I arrive later than he does.

794
00:47:52,320 --> 00:47:54,447
-Get in, miss.
-Pardon?

795
00:47:56,657 --> 00:47:58,826
There's a lot of space, so hop in.

796
00:48:03,247 --> 00:48:04,540
Are you getting in or not?

797
00:48:05,750 --> 00:48:09,712
Well, I…

798
00:48:13,716 --> 00:48:17,845
<i>"A regular employee will never
run into the president at work"?</i>

799
00:48:17,928 --> 00:48:19,305
<i>Whatever.</i>

800
00:48:19,388 --> 00:48:22,600
Mr. Chairman, what brings you
to the office this early in the morning?

801
00:48:23,267 --> 00:48:25,686
It's my company. Am I not allowed to come?

802
00:48:26,395 --> 00:48:28,731
This brat made
a shocking declaration yesterday

803
00:48:28,814 --> 00:48:31,525
but didn't explain it,
so I followed him here.

804
00:48:31,609 --> 00:48:34,445
What is there to explain?
I told you everything yesterday.

805
00:48:34,528 --> 00:48:37,365
So you're really going to marry her?

806
00:48:37,448 --> 00:48:40,117
Sir, let's discuss that upstairs.

807
00:48:50,586 --> 00:48:51,629
You there.

808
00:48:55,091 --> 00:48:56,300
SENIOR RESEARCHER
SHIN HA-RI

809
00:48:56,384 --> 00:48:57,468
Ms. Shin Ha-ri?

810
00:48:57,551 --> 00:48:59,845
<i>What? Why is he calling me?</i>

811
00:48:59,929 --> 00:49:03,349
<i>No, wait, how does he even know my name?</i>

812
00:49:06,769 --> 00:49:07,603
Yes?

813
00:49:08,646 --> 00:49:10,231
You dropped your employee ID.

814
00:49:11,357 --> 00:49:14,276
I see. Why did I drop that?

815
00:49:19,657 --> 00:49:20,908
Can you give it…

816
00:49:20,991 --> 00:49:22,701
Oh, thank you.

817
00:49:24,203 --> 00:49:25,871
<i>Doors closing.</i>

818
00:49:28,457 --> 00:49:29,375
Shin Ha-ri?

819
00:49:33,629 --> 00:49:37,675
Are you really going to marry Young-seo?

820
00:49:37,758 --> 00:49:39,093
Shin Ha-ri.

821
00:49:39,718 --> 00:49:40,761
Shin Ha-ri?

822
00:49:42,346 --> 00:49:44,056
Shin Ha-ri.

823
00:49:44,140 --> 00:49:46,934
EMPLOYEE PERSONAL RECORDS

824
00:49:47,017 --> 00:49:48,185
I was right.

825
00:49:48,811 --> 00:49:50,855
What do you mean, you were right?

826
00:49:50,938 --> 00:49:52,273
That employee back there.

827
00:49:52,356 --> 00:49:54,275
She made the proposal
for Bucket List Fish.

828
00:49:54,358 --> 00:49:55,985
Oh, really?

829
00:49:56,485 --> 00:49:59,613
She's the one you singled out
for coming up with the idea, right?

830
00:49:59,697 --> 00:50:01,490
I remembered her
because her name was unique.

831
00:50:01,574 --> 00:50:03,868
I thought she was quite competent.

832
00:50:04,452 --> 00:50:07,413
-Even aside from the Bucket List Fish--
-Stop talking about work!

833
00:50:08,414 --> 00:50:09,748
What's the big idea?

834
00:50:09,832 --> 00:50:11,167
What do you mean?

835
00:50:11,250 --> 00:50:14,086
You always said blind dates
were a waste of time.

836
00:50:14,670 --> 00:50:17,840
And now you want to get married
after one blind date?

837
00:50:17,923 --> 00:50:20,843
I'm giving you that granddaughter-in-law
you want so badly.

838
00:50:20,926 --> 00:50:22,261
Really?

839
00:50:22,344 --> 00:50:24,763
Does Young-seo want to marry you as well?

840
00:50:29,101 --> 00:50:30,311
What do you think?

841
00:50:31,645 --> 00:50:32,730
About what?

842
00:50:33,564 --> 00:50:37,943
With my face, body, impeccable manners,
and flawless personality,

843
00:50:38,903 --> 00:50:40,237
why would she say no?

844
00:50:40,321 --> 00:50:43,324
You're right! No one would say no

845
00:50:43,407 --> 00:50:45,284
to my handsome grandson!

846
00:50:46,577 --> 00:50:47,745
Look at you.

847
00:50:50,372 --> 00:50:52,082
Who would say no to you?

848
00:50:53,834 --> 00:50:55,794
That's my boy.

849
00:50:56,462 --> 00:51:00,466
Was Young-seo really that good?

850
00:51:01,800 --> 00:51:04,512
I'm not sure, sir.
I didn't get a good look at her.

851
00:51:06,972 --> 00:51:10,976
He lost his parents at a young age

852
00:51:11,477 --> 00:51:12,686
and I was

853
00:51:13,896 --> 00:51:18,651
always too busy to really be there
for him as his grandfather.

854
00:51:19,235 --> 00:51:22,321
How nice would it be

855
00:51:22,905 --> 00:51:27,284
for him to start his own family
and love and care for them?

856
00:51:28,994 --> 00:51:31,413
This goes for you, too.

857
00:51:32,331 --> 00:51:34,083
Aren't you going to get a girlfriend?

858
00:51:35,292 --> 00:51:38,087
Don't just work all the time
like my grandson.

859
00:51:38,170 --> 00:51:42,716
Go find a good girl for yourself
and introduce her to me.

860
00:51:44,718 --> 00:51:45,803
Okay?

861
00:51:47,763 --> 00:51:50,391
You ran into the president?
And in the elevator, of all places?

862
00:51:50,474 --> 00:51:52,977
Yeah! Do you have any idea
how scared I was?

863
00:51:53,769 --> 00:51:58,190
So meet with Mr. Kang as soon as possible
and take care of this situation!

864
00:51:58,274 --> 00:52:01,986
Okay, fine. Don't worry.

865
00:52:02,069 --> 00:52:03,153
Okay.

866
00:52:03,737 --> 00:52:05,239
Things are not looking good.

867
00:52:06,949 --> 00:52:07,908
Are you okay?

868
00:52:07,992 --> 00:52:09,910
I told you not to fool around!

869
00:52:09,994 --> 00:52:11,203
Oh, I'm so sorry.

870
00:52:16,792 --> 00:52:17,793
Hey, kid.

871
00:52:18,877 --> 00:52:21,130
Is it okay to run around
with something like this?

872
00:52:23,632 --> 00:52:24,925
Not okay, right?

873
00:52:25,634 --> 00:52:28,887
If you promise not to do it again,
I'll show you a magic trick.

874
00:52:28,971 --> 00:52:29,847
Promise.

875
00:52:32,099 --> 00:52:33,058
Look.

876
00:52:38,439 --> 00:52:39,607
Ta-da!

877
00:52:39,690 --> 00:52:41,442
-Guess what this is.
-Poop?

878
00:52:42,484 --> 00:52:43,319
Poop?

879
00:52:44,069 --> 00:52:46,614
How does this look like poop?
It's a flower.

880
00:52:46,697 --> 00:52:50,034
Here's the bud,
and right here are the leaves.

881
00:52:51,827 --> 00:52:53,829
Anyway, what I'm trying to say is,

882
00:52:53,912 --> 00:52:56,540
you can't be running around
with things like this.

883
00:52:56,624 --> 00:52:58,584
Somebody might get hurt,

884
00:52:58,667 --> 00:53:01,462
or you might ruin somebody's outfit
that's worth a fortune, okay?

885
00:53:01,545 --> 00:53:03,130
-Okay.
-Good.

886
00:53:04,006 --> 00:53:05,758
Let me pay you for the dry cleaning.

887
00:53:05,841 --> 00:53:09,928
Oh, it's fine. I scribbled more
than he did anyway. Here you go.

888
00:53:11,138 --> 00:53:12,222
Bye.

889
00:53:22,775 --> 00:53:25,611
Oh, right! My car keys and wallet.

890
00:53:29,323 --> 00:53:30,366
Oh, I'm sorry.

891
00:53:33,994 --> 00:53:35,204
Are you all right?

892
00:53:52,805 --> 00:53:54,556
<i>He's handsome as hell.</i>

893
00:53:57,976 --> 00:54:00,229
<i>He's absolutely gorgeous.</i>

894
00:54:01,188 --> 00:54:03,482
<i>I've found my love.</i>

895
00:54:08,278 --> 00:54:11,156
Oh, yes. I'm sorry.

896
00:54:11,240 --> 00:54:12,282
It's no problem.

897
00:54:21,917 --> 00:54:26,088
I want to ask for his number so badly!

898
00:54:29,049 --> 00:54:29,925
Who is this?

899
00:54:31,969 --> 00:54:32,970
Hello?

900
00:54:33,053 --> 00:54:35,222
What? President Kang wants to meet you?

901
00:54:35,305 --> 00:54:37,307
Yeah, he just called me.

902
00:54:37,391 --> 00:54:39,727
That's great!
You can meet and tell him the truth!

903
00:54:41,061 --> 00:54:44,982
My dear friend,
could you go instead of me?

904
00:54:45,065 --> 00:54:46,734
You must be crazy.

905
00:54:46,817 --> 00:54:48,652
I have an important meeting.

906
00:54:48,736 --> 00:54:51,321
Still. How can I go instead? No way.

907
00:54:51,405 --> 00:54:52,489
What if I get caught?

908
00:54:52,573 --> 00:54:53,741
Why would you get caught?

909
00:54:53,824 --> 00:54:56,118
Just go and say you don't like him.
That you won't marry him.

910
00:54:56,201 --> 00:54:58,036
Just say no really clearly. Please?

911
00:55:00,664 --> 00:55:01,957
Forget it.

912
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:06,378
Put off your meeting or take a rain check.
Take care of it yourself.

913
00:55:08,464 --> 00:55:11,008
You remember this scar here?

914
00:55:11,091 --> 00:55:14,386
When I tried to teach that flirty girl
following Min-woo around a lesson,

915
00:55:14,470 --> 00:55:16,263
I slipped and hit my head on a rock.

916
00:55:18,599 --> 00:55:20,934
Of course, I remember.

917
00:55:21,018 --> 00:55:22,895
You bled so much from your head

918
00:55:22,978 --> 00:55:26,023
that you were called the Bloody Head
of Hannam-dong for a while.

919
00:55:36,777 --> 00:55:40,239
Why is it here, of all places?
It's so close to Min-woo's restaurant.

920
00:55:45,286 --> 00:55:47,580
Where is this guy?

921
00:55:47,663 --> 00:55:48,914
CALLING
JIN YOUNG-SEO

922
00:55:57,965 --> 00:55:59,216
Do you have two phones?

923
00:56:02,803 --> 00:56:04,305
Oh, that's--

924
00:56:05,931 --> 00:56:11,395
KANG TAE-MOO'S NUMBER

925
00:56:13,314 --> 00:56:15,733
How dare you just get my number like that?

926
00:56:15,816 --> 00:56:19,528
We're going to get married,
so I should know all your phone numbers.

927
00:56:23,699 --> 00:56:25,951
I'm not planning to marry you.

928
00:56:26,035 --> 00:56:28,120
How can I marry
someone I've only met once?

929
00:56:28,204 --> 00:56:30,539
Then why did you ask me
to get a room with you?

930
00:56:31,332 --> 00:56:33,209
Wasn't it because you liked me?

931
00:56:35,586 --> 00:56:36,587
That was--

932
00:56:36,671 --> 00:56:40,633
And you showing up to the date
means you're willing to get married, no?

933
00:56:40,716 --> 00:56:42,510
I was forced to go.

934
00:56:42,593 --> 00:56:45,680
I hate arranged marriages,
especially for business reasons.

935
00:56:46,347 --> 00:56:49,558
Anyway, please just forget
about all this marriage talk.

936
00:57:01,445 --> 00:57:04,699
Don't be like that.
Let's just get married.

937
00:57:06,158 --> 00:57:08,869
Look here, do you think marriage
is some kind of joke?

938
00:57:08,953 --> 00:57:11,747
How could you ask
just anyone to marry you?

939
00:57:11,831 --> 00:57:15,126
Who says I'm going to marry just anyone?
The person I want to marry…

940
00:57:16,669 --> 00:57:17,503
is you.

941
00:57:20,715 --> 00:57:23,300
No way. I'm not going to marry
someone I barely know.

942
00:57:23,384 --> 00:57:25,511
-Then let's go on just ten dates.
-What?

943
00:57:25,594 --> 00:57:27,513
I'll give you a chance to get to know me.

944
00:57:27,596 --> 00:57:30,016
Once you do,
you'll learn I have a lot of strengths.

945
00:57:31,434 --> 00:57:32,977
And I'm quite good…

946
00:57:35,521 --> 00:57:36,605
at many things.

947
00:57:37,356 --> 00:57:38,774
What do you mean, you're good--

948
00:57:56,167 --> 00:57:58,252
What were you thinking about?

949
00:57:58,335 --> 00:58:00,087
I just meant that I'm good to women.

950
00:58:00,588 --> 00:58:04,091
I'm confident that you won't want
to see other men while seeing me.

951
00:58:06,052 --> 00:58:07,470
Forget it.

952
00:58:09,263 --> 00:58:12,933
I don't want to marry you or date you,

953
00:58:13,017 --> 00:58:15,686
so I hope to never see you again.

954
00:58:29,575 --> 00:58:32,078
Is he crazy or just dying to get married?

955
00:58:32,161 --> 00:58:35,164
Anyway, I think I've said enough
for him to not contact me again.

956
00:58:39,168 --> 00:58:41,837
-Are you done already?
-Let's just go.

957
00:58:53,516 --> 00:58:56,560
Damn it, this is what I was worried about!

958
00:58:57,728 --> 00:58:59,980
I can't run into him looking like this!

